abstract: Gavitt harnessed the burgeoning power of televised sports coverage with his nascent league to produce a powerful conference.
snippet: Gavitt harnessed the burgeoning power of televised sports coverage with his nascent league to produce a powerful conference.
lead_paragraph: Dave Gavitt, the force behind the founding of the Big East Conference in 1979 and the league’s first commissioner when it emerged as a national collegiate basketball powerhouse, died Friday in Providence, R.I., near his hometown, Rumford. He was 73.

abstract: The St. Louis Rams have endured a tumultuous decade of losing and behind-the-scenes strife since their last Super Bowl appearance.
snippet: The St. Louis Rams have endured a tumultuous decade of losing and behind-the-scenes strife since their last Super Bowl appearance.
lead_paragraph: The St. Louis Rams, who face the Giants at MetLife Stadium on Monday night, have not had a winning season in eight years. They finished second to last in the N.F.L. in points allowed four times from 2005 through 2009. They posted a 6-42 record from 2007 through 2009, and although last season’s 7-9 finish offered hope that the franchise was finally headed in the right direction, a season-opening 31-13 loss to Philadelphia proved that the Rams still have a long way to go.

abstract: Days after the 9/11 attacks, researchers at the Columbia Center for Oral History began asking New Yorkers to describe their experience.
snippet: Days after the 9/11 attacks, researchers at the Columbia Center for Oral History began asking New Yorkers to describe their experience.
lead_paragraph: Days after the attacks, researchers at the Columbia Center for Oral History began asking New Yorkers to describe their experience of the most harrowing day in the city's history. The following account, the fall of the trade center told moment by moment and person by person, is drawn from the more than 600 interviews collected in the September 11, 2001 Oral History Project.

abstract: The cellphone provider Three U.K. asked European competition authorities to thwart a collaboration between Telefónica, Vodafone and Everything Everywhere.
snippet: The cellphone provider Three U.K. asked European competition authorities to thwart a collaboration between Telefónica, Vodafone and Everything Everywhere.
lead_paragraph: The mobile phone provider Three U.K. on Wednesday asked the European Commission to block a joint venture of Britain’s three largest operators to sell a common mobile payment and advertising platform for retailers, arguing that the companies’ influence in the market would result in high fees for consumers.
